{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place cumin seeds, coriander seeds and salt into mixing bowl and toast <nobr>6 min\/120°C\/speed <\/nobr>, then grind <nobr>1 min\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer into a small bowl and set aside.","Place fresh coriander and coconut (optional) into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer into a second small bowl and set aside.","Place butter, onions, garlic, cayenne pepper and reserved ground spice mix into mixing bowl, chop <nobr>7 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then sauté <nobr>5 min\/120°C\/speed <\/nobr>. Meanwhile, arrange pumpkin pieces skin side down into Varoma dish and set aside.","Add lentils and water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and cook <nobr>35-40 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>, or until pumpkin is very soft and lentils are soft but not mushy (see Tips). Place covered Varoma aside onto a plate.","Add reserved chopped coriander and coconut, capsicum and 50 g of the crème fraîche into mixing bowl, stir with aid of spatula, then adjust seasoning to taste. Serve curried lentils with steamed pumpkin pieces, garnishing with remaining crème fraîche and a few fresh coriander leaves. Scoop pumpkin off skin as you eat and discard skin."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["3 heaped tsp cumin seeds (10 g)","4 heaped tsp coriander seeds (10 g)","1 ½ tsp salt","30 g fresh coriander, plus extra to garnish","50 g fresh coconut flesh, cut into pieces (2-3 cm) (optional)","80 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces","300 g brown onions, cut into pieces","2 garlic cloves","½ - ¾ tsp ground cayenne pepper","1000 - 1200 g butternut pumpkin, deseeded, cut into 8 pieces with skin on","300 g dried lentils (green or brown)","1000 g water","250 - 300 g preserved roasted red capsicums, cut into pieces (1-2 cm)","130 g crème fraîche              (optional)"]}],"id":"r156347","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-o-fSMAstPTw\/XZVPH7T6mwI\/AAAAAAAAc1Q\/2etJxPABRSIyTewbiMy3iXhzVbZk0EARwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_0eNs30rQcaHkn0Z6.png","title":"Curried lentils and steamed pumpkin","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13 g","fat":"17 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"33 g","calories":"1504 kJ \/ 358 kcal"},"usefulItems":"small bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Lentils vary as to how much water they absorb and how long they take to cook. If lentils are not yet tender after cooking, set Varoma aside, add <nobr>100 g water<\/nobr> and cook <nobr><strong>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1,<\/strong><\/nobr> then, if needed, add another <nobr>100 g water<\/nobr> and repeat.<br>- When cooking for children, use only <nobr>¼ tsp cayenne<\/nobr> pepper, and serve with Greek yoghurt for a cooling effect.<br>- To open a fresh coconut easily, heat it <nobr>5-7 minutes<\/nobr> in a preheated oven (220-240°C) then remove from oven and carefully hit it with a hammer - the shell will crack easily because it will have expanded slightly from the coconut flesh. Cut coconut flesh into <nobr>3 cm pieces<\/nobr> - no need to peel off the thin brown skin for this recipe. Extra coconut pieces can be frozen for up to <nobr>3 months.<\/nobr>","If you prefer more of a dahl texture, blend the curried lentils <nobr><strong>20 sec\/speed 6<\/strong><\/nobr> after cooking.<br>- Use diced fresh red capsicums instead of roasted preserved. This adds a lovely fresh crunch to the curried lentils.<br>- Replace butter with coconut oil and crème fraîche with coconut cream."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","1h 15m","8 portions"]}